\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 * TEXT BUFFER COMMAND (TB): This is an improvement over the 
\par \'d2TT1\'d3 method for implementing a CW/data terminal. Returns number of 
\par transmit characters from KY<text> packets remaining to be sent, as well 
\par as a string containing all available characters, and RX character count. 
\par 
\par * Fixed KY<text> problem in PSK-D/FSK-D modes: Sending packets 
\par during the 4-second idle time was delaying transmit until end of idle time.
\par 
\par * Now recognizing a slashed-zero character from the PC keyboard 
\par (0xD8) in KY<text> packets. Converted to regular zero.
\par 
\par * IC COMMAND: Added CONFIG:MEM 0-9 setting (byte }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 , bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f37\insrsid3036935 ).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.84 / DSP 2.54, 3-22-2010
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 For software developers: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 * NOISE BLANKER LEVEL CONTROL:  Added NL and NL$
\par commands to remotely set DSP and IF blanker levels for main
\par and sub receivers. Refer to the K3 Programmer\rquote s Reference,
\par revision C10 or later. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 Changes related to European FM and Repeater Operation: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * 12.5 AND 25 KHZ VFO INCREMENTS (FOR EU REPEATERS) : 
\par Added 12.5 kHz and 25 kHz step sizes in FM mode. To specify step
\par size, select FM mode, then use the CONFIG:VFO CRS menu entry.
\par 
\par * SQUELCH-CONTROLLED 1750-HZ PL TONE: Some EU 
\par repeaters require a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}1750-Hz PL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} tone burst to open. Previously, an 
\par 0.5-second burst was generated at the start of each transmission. 
\par Now, this tone is only generated if squelch is not already open. 
\par The squelch-controlled PL tone feature can be turned off by
\par setting the PITCH parameter to PL OFF. With either the PL TONE
\par or PL OFF setting, the operator can still do manual PL tone
\par burst as described in the next item.
\par 
\par * MANUALLY CONTROLLED 1750-HZ PL TONE:
\par The operator can now generate a variable-length tone burst 
\par at any time while transmitting by holding PITCH switch. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 * PL {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}TONE{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}DEVIATION{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}RANGE{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} CHANGED: The deviation range 
\par for the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}1750-Hz PL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} tone is now 1.5 to 6.0 kHz. The default, 3.6 kHz,
\par is about 70% of 5 kHz, as recommended for many EU repeaters. 
\par The deviation for sub-audible tones is now stored separately
\par and has a range of 150-600 Hz (default 360 Hz).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.79 / DSP 2.54, 3-5-2010
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * RX ANT SWITCH ALLOWED DURING TX. This is useful if you
\par need to compare signal strength of received signals while sending
\par a repeating CQ message in CW mode. 
\par 
\par * SPURIOUS ERR XXX MESSAGES ELIMINATED: On rare 
\par occasions operators have seen multiple error messages such as
\par ERR BP1, ERR LPF, etc. on power-up. This was caused by a 
\par timing error when communicating with SPI-bus devices, such as
\par the shift registers controlling band-pass and low-pass filters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.78 / DSP 2.54, 3-4-2010
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * MENU ENTRY TEXT ON VFO B:  Eliminated occasional incorrect
\par text appearing on VFO B while scrolling through menu entries.
\par 
\par * AM MODE 9 KHZ TUNING (EU): Corrected occasional PLL errors
\par related to tuning in 9 kHz steps in AM broadcast band.
\par 
\par * AFX \'d2BIN\'d3 MODE: Further stability improvement for the \'d2BIN\'d3 
\par audio effect (selected by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}:AFX). An audio artifact could 
\par occur under certain receive-signal circumstances.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.77 / DSP 2.53, 2-27-2010
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * DIVERSITY MODE MAIN/SUB RECEIVER OFFSET FIXED: 
\par In some cases a small frequency offset between the main and 
\par sub receiver could be introduced due to transmitting while 
\par moving VFO A or the RIT offset. This no longer occurs.
\par 
\par * SUB RECEIVER BAND-PASS FILTER SWITCHING FIXED:
\par If the main and sub receivers were configured for independent
\par band selection (CONFIG:{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}VFO{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}IND{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} = YES), switching the main
\par receiver to any of 17-10 m may have caused an incorrect 
\par band-pass filter to be selected for the sub receiver.
\par 
\par * SYNTHESIZER PLL TABLES UPDATED: Reduces the
\par DDS tuning range slightly to minimize group delay through the 
\par DDS crystal filter. (These tables are located in the 
\par \'d2HFPF0108\'d3 file, part of the firmware release package.)
\par 
\par * AFX \'d2BIN\'d3 MODE FIX: Stability improvement for the \'d2BIN\'d3 
\par audio effect (selected by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}:AFX). Previously, a loud audio
\par artifact could occur under certain receive-signal circumstances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.76 / DSP 2.52, 1-23-2010
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 Changes related to K144XV, transverters, FM, and repeaters:\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 * REPEATER REVerse: If a repeater offset is in use (+/-), 
\par holding REV switches VFO A to the repeater's input frequency. 
\par 
\par * RF POWER BARGRAPH: Now shows *tenths of a milliwatt* when
\par using low-level transverter I/O (applies to both the K144XV and 
\par external transverters). 10 bars = about 1.00 mW at the IF. This 
\par corresponds to about 10 W output when using the K144XV.
\par 
\par * COARSE TUNING WITH XVTR OFFSETS:  Fixed problem with
\par VFO display when using COARSE tuning steps in combination 
\par with a non-zero transverter frequency offset (CONFIG:XVn OFS).
\par 
\par * IMPROVED FM RECEIVE: FM demodulation algorithm
\par refined to reduce signal distortion.
\par 
\par * FM SQUELCH: No longer opens briefly during memory recall.
\par 
\par * "ANT3" REMINDER WHEN K144XV SELECTED: If you switch 
\par to a band configured for use with the Elecraft K144XV internal 2-m
\par module, \'d2ANT3\'d3 is flashed to remind you to use the separate 
\par BNC antenna jack provided on the fan panel, rather than ANT1/2.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 Other new features and improvements:\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 * NR (NOISE REDUCTION) ON/OFF: This is now saved
\par on a per-band/per-receiver basis (same as NB). NR ADJ 
\par (noise reduction setting) is stored independently for each mode.
\par 
\par * TX MESSAGE MEMORY ERASE:  To completely erase a 
\par transmit message buffer, tap REC, then M1-M4, then CLR. 
\par Note that erasing a CW/DATA memory will not erase a DVR 
\par Message assigned to the same M1-M4 switch, and vice-versa. 
\par 
\par * ERR PTT & ERR KEY (rig keyed at power-up): These error 
\par conditions no longer lock out the POWER switch.
\par 
\par * DELAYED MEMORY RECALL (M>V): In CONFIG:MEM 0-9, 
\par tap '1' to select "M>V NOR" or "M>V DLY". NOR is the default,
\par resulting in \'d2live\'d3 memory recall as you rotate VFO A. In the "DLY" 
\par case, the receiver is not updated until you tap M>V a second 
\par time to exit memory recall. You may prefer \'d2DLY\'d3 if you have 
