\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.68 / DSP 2.49, 12-11-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * AF OUTPUT PROTECTION IN AGC-OFF CASE: Moved 
\par threshold up to prevent false triggering on moderate signals.
\par 
\par * The CONFIG:AF LIM menu entry is now visible without setting
\par TECH MD to ON. The AF LIM entry menu sets up an AF output 
\par max level that only applies when AGC is OFF. Recommended
\par value is 18-24. Lower levels provide better protection but 
\par clip sooner. Adjust RF GAIN downward to eliminate clipping
\par on individual signals. Narrow-band filtering can also help.
\par 
\par * Synthesizer parameters updated on 6 m to eliminate 
\par possible PLL unlock when tuning in vicinity of 52 MHz. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.66 / DSP 2.48, 12-4-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * AF OUTPUT PROTECTION: The DSP now automatically 
\par senses when AF output would be so strong as to drive the 
\par speaker or headphone amplifier into the clipping range. If
\par this happens, AF is muted until you reduce signal levels.
\par (One possible source of excessive audio was a DSP internal
\par overrange, which could result in a very loud audio burst. 
\par DSP code has been changed to eliminate such cases.)
\par 
\par * Increased VCO settling time by 1 ms to eliminate a slight 
\par chirp noted by some operators (extremely rare).
\par 
\par * Increased SPI bus timing delays on power-up. May eliminate
\par spurious error messages (such as \'d2ERR AT3\'d3) that could 
\par occur due to SPI bus loading by multiple option modules.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.63, 11-20-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935 
\par * PTT USE WITH DVR: If the KDVR3 menu entry \lquote 1\rquote  tap option
\par is set to AUTOPTT (the default), then PTT behaves as follows:
\par 
\par   - If you start DVR message play first (by tapping M1-M4), }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\insrsid3036935 then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid3036935  
\par     assert PTT during the message, DVR play will be cancelled.
\par 
\par   - If you assert PTT first, then play a DVR message, it will
\par     play normally, and will complete even if you let go of PTT.
\par 
\par You can also cancel DVR message play by tapping REC, as usual, 
\par whether PTT is asserted or not. (Or cancel from a computer
\par using the \'d2RX;\'d3 command \endash  see below.)
\par 
\par Note: If the KDVR3 menu entry \lquote 1\rquote  tap option is set to
\par USE PTT, then PTT is required as a qualifier for DVR 
\par message play. In this case, releasing PTT in the middle
\par of a DVR message will cancel it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\insrsid3036935 Remote Control Command Changes:\line 
