\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 New Feature: Synchronous AM Receive
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * SYNCHRONOUS AM: Outperforms regular AM during selective fading.
\par Provides optional automatic VFO tracking of AM signals up to +/- 2.5 kHz. 
\par 
\par Select AM mode, then hold }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 ALT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  to select AM}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 -S}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 . The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 -S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  icon flashes 
\par slowly if the signal is noisy. Select }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 AM-S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 LSB}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 USB}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  using }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 SHIFT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 ; 
\par one of the two sidebands may reduce QRM. Sync AM also works with 
\par diversity receive. (Note: Some AM broadcast stations encode their 
\par carrier, resulting in a low-pitched noise when Sync AM is turned on.)
\par 
\par With Sync AM you can tune manually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  or use automatic VFO tracking:
\par 
\par -- If tuning }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 manually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 , you need to tune to within +/- 10 Hz of the actual 
\par    carrier frequency, at which point the K3 will phase-lock to the carrier.
\par 
\par -- To enable }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 VFO tracking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 , tap }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 CWT}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 , which turns on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  icon. Or, 
\par    tap }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 SPOT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  to engage VFO tracking just long enough to lock. When
\par    tracking is on, the VFO may \'d2hunt\'d3 slowly across a span of several Hz. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 IMPORTANT:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935   For AM QSOs, use }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} mode when VFO tracking is 

