\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.52 / DSP 2.43 / K3 Utility 1.2.10.27, 10-28-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par Misc. Improvements:\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * Eliminated some audio artifacts noted during control changes.
\par 
\par * Eliminated interruption of transmitted CW signal when certain switches 
\par were tapped, including RIT, during external keying.
\par 
\par * VFO LOCK PREVENTS COARSE STEPS VIA OFFSET CONTROL: 
\par Normally, you can use the RIT/XIT offset control to move VFO A in coarse
\par steps if (1) RIT and XIT are both turned off, and (2) CONFIG:VFO OFS 
\par is set to ON. Now, these conditions are overridden if the VFO is locked.
\par 
\par * AUTO-NOTCH IN SSB MODE EASIER TO TURN ON/OFF: The NTCH
\par switch now behaves differently in SSB mode. Tapping it turns auto notch
\par on-off, rather than cycling through off-auto-manual notch. (To turn on
\par manual notch in SSB mode, hold the NTCH/MANUAL switch.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 New Feature: Main/Sub AF Mixing Menu Entry\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * AUDIO MIXING CONTROL ADDED: Normally, main receiver audio is 
\par heard in the left audio channel, and sub in the right. Using the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:L-MIX-R}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par menu entry, you can now put main in both channels while leaving sub in only 
\par one (or vice-versa, or even put both receivers in both channels). Another
\par benefit of this change is that AFX (audio effects) can be used even while the
\par sub receiver is turned on. (AFX, if turned on, will apply to any receiver whose
\par audio is mapped both left and right.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Notes:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935   Applies only to non-diversity mode use of the sub receiver. (In 
\par diversity mode, left/right differentiation is maximized for best results.)
\par You\rquote ll need stereo headphones or speakers to listen to stereo 
\par separation and audio effects. Set CONFIG:SPKRS to 2 if using stereo
\par speakers. (Headphones will always work with stereo material unless
\par SPKRS is set to 1 *and* CONFIG:SPKR+PH is set to ON.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 New Feature: User-Defined Switch Functions (e.g., \'d2SPLIT+2\'d3)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * SWITCH MACROS: You can now program the K3\rquote s PF1-2 and M1-M4
\par switches to execute K3 remote control sequences, or \'d2macros.\'d3 They
\par are created and tested using K3 Utility (rev. 1.2.10.26 or later). Once
\par macros are finished, you can send them to the K3, where they
\par can be assigned to any programmable function switch. The K3 
\par Programmer\rquote s Reference, revision C6, has a number of sample macros 
\par and further details.
\par 
\par Example: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 A>B, A>B, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, VFO B up 2 kHz, RIT/XIT off, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 assigned to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 PF1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par 
\par To create a macro and assign it to a K3 front panel switch, you\rquote ll 
\par need to complete steps 1-8 below. Once you\rquote ve been through the 
\par process one time, you\rquote ll find creating or modifying macros very easy.
\par 
\par 1. Run }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 K3 Utility}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 .
\par 2. Click on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Command Tester/K3 Macros}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  tab.
\par 3. Click on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Edit Macros}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  button. This pops up the macro edit window.
\par 4. In MACRO 1\rquote s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Macro Label}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935   field, enter the label \'d2{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}+2\'d3.
\par 5. In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Macro Commands }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 field, enter:
\par 
\par     SWT13;SWT13;FT1;UPB5;RT0;XT0;
\par 
\par (The number }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  in the \'d2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 UPB5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 \'d3 command is not a value in kHz;
\par it is an index into a table of step sizes. UPB5 moves VFO B up 2 kHz,
\par DNB5 moves it down 2 kHz, etc. There are similar commands for
\par VFO A. For the full list, see the \'d2DN\'d3 (down) command in the 
\par Programmer\rquote s Reference.)
\par 
\par 6. Click on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Send Macros 1-8 To K3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 .
\par 7. At the K3, locate }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:MACRO x}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  menu entry, and tap \lquote 1\rquote  if
\par    the menu entry label is not already \'d2MACRO 1\'d3.
\par 8. Hold PF1 to assign PF1 to MACRO 1. Exit the menu.
\par 
\par From then on, PF1 will flash \'d2SPLIT+2\'d3 and execute the above sequence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935   M1-M4 cannot be used simultaneously for both message play
\par and macros. To revert an Mx switch back to message play, first
\par switch to CW mode, then tap Mx, tap REC, and tap  Mx again. This
