\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Remote Control Command Changes: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * MP COMMAND ACCESS ADDED TO: LCD ADJ, LCD BRT, LED BRT. 
\par This allows creation of a switch macro that does LCD DIM/BRT, for example.
\par You can also use MP to control the new Main/Sub Mix menu entry.
\par See K3 Programmer\rquote s Reference, revision C6 or later.
\par 
\par * Switch- and menu-emulation commands now run to completion
\par before subsequent commands in the buffer are handled. This means
\par that applications and macros using these emulation commands no
\par longer have to insert delays (such as dummy \lquote ;\rquote ) commands. 
\par 
\par * \'d2BW\'d3 (BANDWIDTH) REMOTE CONTROL COMMAND ADDED: This is a 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 non-modal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  version of FW (it work with either the K30 or K31
\par meta-command in effect). 
\par 
\par * \'d2SB\'d3 REMOTE CONTROL COMMAND ADDED (sub receiver on/off).
\par 
\par * \'d2LN\'d3 REMOTE CONTROL COMMAND ADDED (link/unlink VFOs).
\par 
\par * \'d2KYW\'d3 VARIATION OF \'d2KY<MSG>\'d3 COMMAND ADDED:  Waits until 
\par the current message has been sent before processing other host commands.
\par This is useful if the \'d2KY<MSG>\'d3 command is followed by other 
\par commands, such as \'d2KS\'d3 (keyer speed control). See examples in 
\par Programmer\rquote s Reference.
\par 
\par * \'d2SWT\'d3 / \'d2SWH\'d3 COMMAND IMPROVEMENT: These switch emulation
\par commands are now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 non-modal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  (they will work with either the K30 or K31
\par meta-command in effect). 
\par 
\par * \'d2DN\'d3 / \'d2UP\'d3 COMMANDS IMPROVED: These VFO movement commands
\par have extended functionality and are now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 non-modal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  (they will work with
\par any of the K2x meta commands in effect).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.44 / DSP 2.38, 10-14-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * TUNE & ATU TUNE NOW WORK IN DATA A MODE/SPLIT:
\par TUNE and ATU TUNE were producing no power output in DATA A
\par /SPLIT, even though normal transmit worked correctly.
\par 
\par * NON-FM SQUELCH WORKING ON A/B VFO SWAP:  In some
\par cases in SSB or CW mode, squelch could end up permanently
\par closed when swapping VFOs and listening to strong signals.
\par 
\par * NOISE REDUCTION CONTROL: Internal self-tests added to 
\par further reduce the likelihood of AF artifacts or continuous switch 
\par feedback tones when turning NR on/off, changing bands, etc.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 3.42 / DSP 2.37, 10-06-2009
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * POLLING PROBLEM WITH HRD FIXED: With no sub receiver
\par installed, HRD (Ham Radio Deluxe) was still able to poll for its
\par revision number, causing a timeout.  
\par 
\par * SQUELCH CAN BE SET FULLY CLOCKWISE: In some cases
\par rotating the squelch pot fully clockwise would open the squelch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.41 / DSP 2.37, 10-02-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * IMPROVED RX LOW-FREQUENCY RESPONSE in AM/SSB/CW MODES: 
\par Most noticeable with hi-fidelity headphones or large speakers. NORMalizing 
\par the DSP passband still sets the cutoff to about 100 Hz, but DSP controls can
\par be adjusted to provide a lower response. RX EQ can enhance bass further. 
\par 
\par * NO RX EQ OR TX EQ IN DATA MODES: That is, the response is flat.
\par The RX EQ and TX EQ menu entries now affect only the other modes.
\par 
\par * "LIVE" MEMORY RECALL (M>V):  If you tap M>V, then start rotating
\par VFO A to select a memory, the K3 will now switch to the band/mode 
\par of each memory. Exit memory recall by tapping M>V a second time.
\par 
\par * VFO COARSE STEP ROUNDING: Tap '1' in the VFO CRS menu entry 
\par to select RND=NO or YES. If YES, the VFO frequency will be rounded off
\par during COARSE tuning. This menu entry also sets the per-mode COARSE 
\par step size. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  The RIT/XIT control moves the VFO in coarse steps if 
\par RIT and XIT are not in use (use CONFIG:VFO OFS to turn this on/off).
\par 
\par * SSB COARSE STEP SIZE OPTIONS NOW 0.1, 0.5, 1.0, and 2.5 kHz:
\par Replaced 5.0 kHz with 0.5 kHz.
\par 
\par * CWT (TUNING AID) NOW INDEPENDENT FOR CW & DATA.
\par 
\par * RF GAIN CALIBRATION PROCEDURE UPDATED:  You\rquote ll need the 
\par latest revision of K3 Utility and a 50-microvolt signal source (e.g., an XG2).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * SUB RX NOISE BLANKER NOW FULLY INDEPENDENT OF {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}:
\par This includes the on/off state and NB LEVEL settings. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  Set
\par CONFIG:NB SAVE to YES to preserve your per-band NB on/off settings.
\par 
\par * DSP INTERNAL STATUS MONITORING: In the TECH MD menu entry,
\par tapping 1 (main) or 2 (sub) displays DSP status information. If it is \'d2FFFF\'d3, 
\par no error has been detected. Tapping CLR resets the data to \'d2FFFF\'d3.
\par 
\par * CHANNEL HOPPING IN FM MODE LOADS REPEATER SETTINGS: \line Repeater offsets and PL tones are now loaded during scanning/hopping.
\par 
\par * PL TONE DEVIATION ADJUSTABLE: Tapping '1' in CONFIG:FM DEV 
\par allows setting PL tone deviation (300-600 Hz in 30-Hz steps; default, 360 Hz).
\par 
\par * EU REPEATER 1750 HZ PL TONE BURST:  If a 1750 Hz PL TONE is
\par selected, a 500 ms tone burst will be sent on each PTT activation.
\par 
\par * EXTENDED 6-METER TUNING RANGE: The VFO can now be tuned 
\par down to 44 MHz to monitor signals that may be correlated with 6-meter 
\par band openings. Loss increases rapidly below 49 MHz (-34 dB at 45 MHz),
\par so a preamp (e.g., the Elecraft PR6) may be needed to obtain a useful NF.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.30 / DSP 2.27, 9-2-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * RF Gain control now smoother if RF Gain Calibration has been
\par performed.  See K3 Utility Help for details.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * FIXED NOISE BLANKER SWITCHING IN BSET MODE: You can
\par now independently turn the noise blanker (NB) on/off for the sub
\par receiver in all cases. Previously, the NB switch was locked out
\par in some cases in BSET mode.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * DVR TRANSMIT WITH MANUAL PTT: Normally, playing a DVR 
\par TX message (M1-M4) automatically asserts PTT and goes into 
\par transmit mode. Now, you can manually assert PTT prior to playing
\par DVR messages, if necessary. (This might be required to meet external 
\par equipment switching requirements at some stations.) To do this: in the 
\par CONFIG:KDVR3 menu entry, tap \lquote 1\rquote  until you see \'d2USE PTT\'d3. 
\par (This setting is ignored in VOX mode.)
\par 
\par * ELIMINATED AUDIO NOISE BURST WITH NR + AUTONOTCH:
\par Very rarely, the combination of NR and autonotch, in the presence of
\par a strong signal, could result in a loud audio artifact.
\par 
\par * MORE NR (DENOISER) SETTINGS:  There are now 32 NR settings.
\par F1-x to F4-x originally appeared in firmware revision 3.27, and are 
\par recommended for most applications. F5-x to F8-x are the same as
\par F1-x to F4-x from firmware revision 3.25. They provide a varying mix 
\par between processed (\'d2wet\'d3) and unprocessed (\'d2dry\'d3) audio. When x is 1, 
\par the mix is mostly "dry"; when x is 4, it's 100% "wet". A small letter \'d2m\'d3 
\par (e.g. "NR m F5-1") reminds you that "mixed" settings are in use.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note 1:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  When you\rquote re experimenting with different NR ADJ settings, allow 
\par 1 to 3 seconds for the DSP to fully adapt to present signal conditions. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note 2:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  F5-x and higher NR settings may alter the amplitude of 
\par single-tone (CW) signals somewhat, depending on the pitch. Voice 
\par signals are less affected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
