\par * SHIFT=.01 BUG FIXED W/LOW SIDETONE PITCH (300 Hz).
\par 
\par * VFOS TUNE DOWN TO 490 KHZ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For Software Developers:
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * "IS" COMMAND BUG IN 10-HZ MODE FIXED.
\par 
\par * FINE SHIFT BIT ADDED TO "IC" COMMAND: Byte e, bit 6.
\par 
\par * "MN" GET COMMAND IMPLEMENTED.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.25 / DSP 2.21, 8-11-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 New Features:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * NOISE REDUCTION (NR) IMPROVEMENTS: Our new NR
\par algorithm has less impact on signal strength, and should no 
\par longer make some weak signals \'d2disappear\'d3 due to over-processing.
\par We may fine-tune the algorithm in future releases, based on
\par operator evaluation, but we\rquote ve have good reports from early testers.
\par 
\par * VFO TUNING NOISE REDUCTION: Some operators have reported
\par hearing noise on 60, 10, or 6 meters when tuning the VFO under
\par very quiet conditions. If you experience this, try the following:
\par In the CONFIG:VCO MD menu entry, tap \lquote 1\rquote  until you see \'d2SPI 2\'d3
\par (the default is \'d2SPI 1\'d3). This alters the timing of data sent to the 
\par synthesizer, which in turn changes the spectrum of SPI-bus
\par signal noise. It has no impact on performance. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 You will also need to
\par add two resistors and two diodes to the bottom of the RF board
\par (see application note on our K3 modifications web page).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par 
\par * AUTOMATIC RECEIVER FRONT END PROTECTION:  If the K3 is
\par operated too close to high-power transmitters, it\rquote s possible to damage 
\par some receiver components. While this rarely happens, we\rquote ve taken
\par steps to prevent it by sensing a high-current condition at the mixer
\par post-amplifier (Q8/Q9) and automatically turning off the preamp and,
\par if necessary, turning on the attenuator. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 You will need to add one 
\par jumper wire on the bottom of the RF board (see application note 
\par on our K3 modifications web page).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  If you don\rquote t add the jumper, 
\par operation will be unchanged; firmware can sense whether or not 
\par you\rquote ve installed the jumper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * 10-HZ PASSBAND SHIFT STEPS (EXPERIMENTAL):
\par If CONFIG:PB CTRL is set to SHIFT=.01 for a given operating mode, 
\par the SHIFT control will provide .01 kHz (10 Hz) steps rather than the 
\par original .05 kHz (50 Hz). Especially useful with narrow filter bandwidths.
\par This feature is experimental and has some limitations at present:
\par Applies to CW and DATA only; LOCUT/HICUT cannot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 be used when
\par 10-Hz SHIFT steps are in effect; WIDTH steps remain 50 Hz in all cases. 
\par Not compatible with spur removal function yet (CONFIG:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 SIG RMV); 
\par signals mapped out may reappear.
\par 
\par * CW SPEED DISPLAYED WITH DECODED CW TEXT: If the TEXT 
\par DEC switch parameter is set to WPM CHK (using VFO B), the speed of 
\par on-air CW signals will be shown, along with a small window of CW text. 
\par You might see \'d218w.  CQ\'c9\'d3, where \'d218w.\'d3 means 18 WPM. Both text 
\par decode and WPM display accuracy can be improved by using narrow 
\par filtering and by careful adjustment of the \'d2THR\'d3 (threshold) parameter 
\par (set with VFO A when the TEXT DEC switch is pressed).
\par 
\par * RF GAIN CALIBRATION: The K3\rquote s hardware AGC circuitry can now be 
\par calibrated. This may improve both S-meter and RF GAIN control accuracy. 
\par To do RF GAIN calibration, use revision 1.2.7.24 or later of K3 Utility (use the 
\par RF GAIN calibration function, under Configuration). This procedure calibrates
\par both main and sub receivers. A signal source is required. Future firmware 
\par revisions will further improve accuracy, using the calibration data stored
\par by this procedure.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Misc. Improvements:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * "SK" IS NO LONGER DISPLAYED IN RESPONSE TO NOISE 
\par DURING CW DECODE. Incorrect characters are now displayed as \lquote *\rquote .
\par 
\par * 6 METER SCANNING NO LONGER PROHIBITED. Scanning is limited 
\par to the 6-m {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}U.S.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} ham band (50-54). Exception: In some countries the K3 won\rquote t
\par operate on 6 m at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * TTY CENTER FREQ NOW DISPLAYED CORRECTLY: In FSK-D
\par and AFSK-A modes, rotating SHIFT now shows the exact center
\par pitch (when indicated by an asterisk). The four available center
\par pitches are 1000, 1360, 1530, and 2210 Hz. Previously the pitch was
\par rounded down to the nearest 50 Hz.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For Software Developers:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * "RO" COMMAND (RIT/XIT OFFSET READ/SET) ADDED. This
\par command provides a more direct way to set up the RIT/XIT offset,
\par as an alternative to \'d2RU\'d3 and \'d2RD\'d3. Set/Response format: 
\par ROsxxxx; where s is +/-, and xxxx is 0000-9999.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Troubleshooting Aid:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * KAT3 \'d2NOT INST\'d3 setting is now global. If you set CONFIG:KAT3 to 
\par NOT INST for the present band/antenna, it applies to all bands/antennas.
\par Similarly, if you change the setting from NOT INST to any other setting,
\par all per-band/per-antenna ATU mode data is restored. This change is
\par useful if you need to remove a KAT3 module for troubleshooting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 3.19 / DSP 2.17, 6-14-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * POWER-RELATED CONTROL LOCK: The PWR, MIC, and CMP controls
\par can be locked by tapping '1' in CONFIG:PWR_SET. This is useful in 
\par some contests, such as Field Day, where a carefully-set up K3 might be
\par used by multiple operators. Accessing a locked control flashes "LOCKED". SPD/DELAY/MON functions are still accessible. Tapping a locked knob still 
\par displays the current parameter value, even though you can't change it.
\par 
\par * AUTOMATIC CW VFO OFFSET ON MODE CHANGE: Allows switching 
\par quickly between SSB and CW mode without either you or the other station 
\par having to re-tune the VFO (often done on 6 meters and transverter bands). 
\par First, locate CONFIG:CW WGHT and tap \lquote 5\rquote  on the keypad until you see
\par \'d2VFO OFS\'d3. From then on, when switching to CW mode from any other 
\par mode, the VFO will be offset by an amount equal to your sidetone pitch 
\par (as set using the PITCH switch in CW mode). If the sideband most recently 
\par used on this band is USB, the VFO will be shifted UP; if it was LSB, the 
\par VFO will be shifted DOWN.
\par 
\par Note: If you make frequent use of this feature, you may want to
\par use CW reverse on bands where you use USB, and CW normal
\par on bands where you use LSB. This results in perfect pitch matching
\par when listening to a CW signal and switching from SSB to CW. 
\par 
\par * GHZ TRANSVERTER DIGITS are now shown for two seconds on any 
\par band change, if applicable (i.e. if transverter frequency is set for > 999 
\par MHz in menu entry CONFIG:XVn RF). This serves as a reminder of
\par the actual band in use, since the MHz digits alone can be ambiguous.
\par 
\par * AM MODULATION: Now closer to 100%.
\par 
\par * TUNING VFO FROM ONE BAND TO ANOTHER WITH BANDS 
\par MAPPED OUT: This no longer alters CONFIG:BND MAP settings.
\par 
\par * SYNTH UNLOCK WHEN USING PTT/CW: When using PTT, cancelling 
\par CW message play by tapping the key or keyer was sometimes causing the
\par synthesizer to unlock.
\par 
\par * CW SIDETONE STUCK WITH PTT: When using PTT, cancelling CW 
\par message play during a CW element was sometimes leaving sidetone on. 
\par 
\par * 6M CAN BE PERMANENTLY DISABLED: This is required for some 
\par countries. This would normally be done at the factory, but can also be
\par done in the field with a PC program (contact customer support if
\par interested).
\par 
\par * MAX POWER LEVEL NOW 110 W (was 120 W): This is intended
\par to reduce the possibility of excess KPA3 operating current on some 
\par bands. This might have occurred when using a high power setting 
\par along with low power supply voltage and/or a high load SWR. 
\par (}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 : The recommended maximum power setting is still 100 W.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For Software Developers:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * MONITOR LEVEL (ML) COMMAND: MLxxx (000-060 where 000 is 
\par OFF, in effect). Applied per-mode.
\par 
\par * IC COMMAND NOW HAS A "TX MSG PLAYING" FLAG. Byte "}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 " bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
