\par applies to a 100-Hz VFO segment, e.g. from 28135.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  to 28135.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 39}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 , so
\par you\rquote ll have to tune slowly through that 100-Hz range using 10-Hz steps to
\par make sure the birdie has been completely removed. Once you\rquote re finished,
\par you may still hear a slightly tuning artifact as you tune through this range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 NOTE:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  In most cases, you\rquote ll need to apply SIG RMV to at least two adjacent
\par 100-Hz VFO segments. Also, if you use more than one filter or SHIFT 
\par setting in the present operating mode, you\rquote ll probably need to map out the
\par birdie more than one time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 TO UNDO SIG RMV:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  If you tap CLR while
\par you\rquote re in the SIG RMV menu entry, all birdie information for the present
\par band will be permanently deleted. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 SSB MODE ALTERNATIVE:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  In SSB
\par modes, simply leaving AUTO NOTCH on may be effective.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Limitations:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  SIG RMV is experimental. It applies only to the main receiver,
\par at present, and only in CW/SSB/DATA modes. Do not attempt to remove
\par birdies on transverter bands; instead, remove them on the I.F. band used.
\par On each band from 160-6 m, up to 60 birdies can be removed. But as 
\par mentioned above, each one may have to be mapped out from adjacent
\par VFO segments as well as for different filter and SHIFT settings. So the 
\par practical number of birdies that can be removed is more like 5 to 20 per
\par band. A small audible tuning artifact may remain after removing strong birdies.
\par Changing {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}REF{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}CAL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or your sidetone pitch may make birdies re-appear.
\par In this case, you might want to tap CLR within SIG RMV to delete the data
\par for the present band, then start over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par Misc. improvements
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * SSB/DATA POWER OUTPUT CONTROL: Power-setting accuracy has 
\par been significantly improved over previous releases.
\par 
\par * AFSK A TRANSMIT NOISE ELIMINATED: Under certain circumstances, 
\par such as with DUAL PB turned on, the AFSK A transmit signal could be 
\par modulated by low-level audio noise. This has now been eliminated.
\par 
\par * PTT-CW RELEASE FIXED: When PTT is used to \'d2arm\'d3 CW transmit, e.g. with
\par a footswitch, releasing PTT in the middle of keying now disables transmit.
\par Note: This does not apply if VOX is turned on in CW mode. In this case, the
\par keying inputs are always \'d2live,\'d3 i.e. you can hit the key to transmit whether
\par PTT was used or not.
\par 
\par * TX LED: This LED now only turns on if power output is actually enabled. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * EXTENDED TRANSVERTER BAND COVERAGE: When 10 meters is used}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 as a transverter-band I.F., the upper end is no longer limited to 30 MHz. In the
\par case of a transverter band set up for 2 meters (nominally 144-146 MHz), this
\par allows tuning a bit higher than 146 MHz, if desired. The 10-meter
\par band-pass filter falls off pretty quickly above 30 MHz. But the extended range 
\par may be useful for hitting repeaters with in/out in the 146 to 147 MHz range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For software developers
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * IC COMMAND SHOWS SUB ON/OFF STATUS: Byte b, bit 0. This is 
\par more reliable than the SUB ON bit in the DS response. \'d2IC\'d3 also as the 
\par advantage that "K31" mode need not be in effect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.82 / DSP 2.00, 2-9-2009
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Data Mode Changes:
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * AFSK MODE TRANSMIT FILTERING: Some K3 owners have reported 
\par hearing noise on their RTTY transmit signal when using AFSK-A mode. Possible 
\par sources of noise include RFI, ground loops, low AF level, or poor mark/space 
\par transition shaping by software. The effects of noise from many sources can
\par be eliminated by using a narrow, constant-delay transmit filter (DSP).
\par To enable this filter, set CONFIG:{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}AFSK{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}TX{\*\xmlclose}, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}FIL{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}ON{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} (default is OFF).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * SSB/DATA-A/AFSK-A TRANSMIT POWER LEVEL: Power output in these
\par modes now more closely the requested power. Because of this, we recommend 
\par setting CONFIG:TXG VCE to 0.0 dB after loading this release, then adjusting
\par the value only if necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * DATA MODE ALC METERING: ALC metering for DATA-A and AFSK-A 
\par modes has been adjusted to make the transmit audio level easier to adjust.
\par As before, the recommended audio level for transmission is 4 to 5 bars. 
\par 3 bars will appear as soon the minimum required level for good S/N ratio 
\par has been reached.
\par 
\par * FSK POLARITY MENU ENTRY: Setting CONFIG:FSK POL to 0 reverses 
\par RTTY data polarity (}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 applies only to FSK-D mode transmit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 ) . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  If you use
\par the ALT switch to select DATA REV mode, this reverses }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 both}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  RX and TX
\par tones, in both AFSK-A and FSK-D modes. This should rarely be required.
\par FSK POL can be used by itself or in combination with DATA REV.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Misc. Changes:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * DVR MESSAGE CANCEL WITH PTT OR VOX: Both one-time and repeating
\par DVR transmit message play can now be cancelled cleanly with either
\par PTT or VOX.
\par 
\par * AM MODE SPEECH COMPRESSION: Speech compression is now
\par available in AM mode. This can add punch to your AM signal. As with any 
\par type of compression, it should be used only when necessary.
\par 
\par * FM TX DEVIATION: This is now more accurate. Previous versions could 
\par underdeviate by as much as 1 kHz. Setting is now accurate from 3.0 kHz to
\par 5.0 kHz of deviation when modulated by 1 kHz tone with 5 bars of ALC
\par indicated.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For software developers:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * \'d2BN\'d3 COMMAND ADDED (Band Number). GET only. This command returns 
\par the K3\rquote s present band }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 number}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  (0-10 = 160 m - 6 m, 11-15 reserved for
\par future use, 16-24 = XVTR bands 1-9). It is useful for software applications
\par that need to know if the operator has tuned the VFO across a logical band 
\par boundary. This eliminates the need for applications to keep track of what the
\par K3\rquote s internal band boundaries are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.80 / DSP 1.99, 1-23-2009
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * AM POWER LEVEL NO LONGER DRIFTS: AM power setting is now more
\par accurate, and doesn\rquote t change over time. 
\par 
\par * AM TRANSMIT SIGNAL NO LONGER OVERMODULATED: AM ALC and
\par audio signal levels have been adjusted to provide a very clean transmit signal. 
\par 
\par * DVR TERMINATION VIA PTT: Activating PTT will immediately stop DVR
\par transmit message playback.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * CWT (CW TUNING AID) ON/OFF STATE SAVED: If you turn CWT on, it will 
\par always turn on when you return to the applicable mode (e.g. CW).
\par 
\par * MANUAL ATU L/C CHANGES ARE SAVED (per-band, per-antenna, 
\par just like when doing an auto-tune). Manual ATU adjustment is possible when
\par CONFIG:KAT3 is set to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 LC SET}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  (see owner\rquote s manual). Previously, manual 
\par L/C changes were lost when the KAT3 mode was returned to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 AUTO}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 BYP}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 .
\par 
\par * ALC METERING AVAILABLE IN FM MODE: Previously, in FM mode the
\par ALC meter scale was fixed at 7 bars. 
\par 
\par * CROSS-MODE {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} : When using cross-mode {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} (e.g. LSB/USB) with 
\par the sub-RX ON, the use of TUNE would sometimes result in an incorrect sub 
\par receiver synthesizer frequency.
\par 
\par * SPOT and PITCH switches work correctly with switch feedback tones enabled.
\par Switch feedback tones are not used for these switches since a tone is generated
\par anyway. Previously, the sidetone would sometimes not be heard.
\par 
\par * XVx MENU ENTRY BEHAVIOR CORRECTED:  Previously, adjusting these 
\par menu entries would sometimes change the mode or frequency of the VFOs.
\par 
\par * VFO CTS MENU ENTRY: A change in the VFO counts-per-turn setting now 
\par takes effect immediately, rather than requiring a mode change or power cycle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.78 / DSP 1.98, 1-8-2009
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * SIGN-ON BANNER SUPPORT (for your callsign, etc.): If you specify a sign-on
\par message (using K3 Utility), it will be displayed when you turn your K3 on. This
\par might include your call sign, serial number, etc. K3 Utililty revision 1.1.12.29 or
\par later is required. Click on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Configuration}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  tab, then click on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Edit Sign-On 
\par Banner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 . Up to 22 characters can be entered. If you delete all characters from 
\par the message, no banner will be shown.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Misc. Changes:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * SSB SPLIT TX AUDIO PROBLEM CORRECTED: In certain cases (ESSB,
\par VFO A/B on different modes, or SUB turned on), going into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} mode would
\par result in no SSB transmit audio, or an incorrect transmit audio passband.
\par 
\par * VFO COUNTS PER TURN CORRECT AFTER EXIT FROM COARSE TUNING:
\par Previously, if you had CONFIG:VFO CTS set to 400 or 200, selecting COARSE
\par tuning would leave VFO counts/turn at 100 even after switching to another tuning
\par rate. (100 counts per turn is used for coarse tuning due to the large step sizes.)
\par 
\par * SUB/MAIN AF BALANCE CONTROL: {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Main{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and sub RX audio are now correctly
\par restored when the sub is turned on/off, etc. Previously, either receiver might
\par have remained muted after sub on/off when SUB AF was set up as BALANCE.
\par 
\par * DVR WITH COMPUTER CONTROL (HRD, ETC.): Running HRD (and some 
\par other PC applications) no longer terminates DVR record/play. Some programs
\par were polling every second or so for the DVR\rquote s firmware revision, which stops the
\par DVR. The K3 MCU now handles this command in all cases without DVR 
\par interruption.
\par 
\par * AM DSP BANDWIDTH DISPLAY NOW SHOWS *AF* BANDWIDTH, NOT IF. We 
\par originally showed the IF bandwidth in AM mode since some operators might be
\par thinking about the underlying AM-mode implementation (i.e., the IF bandwidth 
\par has to be twice the AF bandwidth in this mode). But this was causing a lot of 
\par confusion, and was inconsistent with the way the DSP bandwidth control works in 
\par other modes, where the *AF* bandwidth is displayed. Also, LO and HI CUT show 
\par AF cutoff points \endash  not IF \endash  even in AM mode. So we now consistently define the 
\par function of all DSP controls as showing AF frequencies/bandwidths. Note: In AM 
\par mode, tapping XFIL will still show the *crystal filter* bandwidth, not the DSP BW.
\par So if you select a 6-kHz crystal filter by tapping XFIL, you\rquote ll see \'d2FL2 6.00\'d3 displayed
\par (for example). But the DSP width control now be at a starting point of 3.00 kHz.
\par Also see related change to \'d2FW\'d3 remote-control command.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For software developers:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * AM-MODE "FW" COMMAND CHANGE: The filter bandwidth command (\'d2FW\'d3)
\par was reporting the IF bandwidth in AM mode (multiplying by two) which was confusing
\par for users of some PC applications. It now reports the DSP (AF) bandwidth in AM 
\par mode. As with the manual WIDTH control, the IF bandwidth is set to approximately
\par twice the AF bandwidth when an \'d2FW\'d3 set command is sent. (Note that \'d2K31\'d3 mode
\par must be in effect in order to use \'d2FW\'d3 to get/set actual bandwidths.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * ENTERING SPLIT CROSS-MODE VIA "FT;": This no longer results in icon flash, 
\par so no dummy SWT command is needed to cancel it. (When split is turned on
\par using the K3\rquote s {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} switch, the cross-mode warning flash is still present.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 K3 Factory Test Changes:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * LOST KPA3 12V SENSE THRESHOLD IS NOW 0.2 V: This allows for possible 
\par future changes to the 12V PA sense circuitry (diode, etc.).
\par 
\par * ADC REF MENU PARAMETER NOW SAVED ON MENU EXIT: Previously it
\par was saved only on power-down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.76 / DSP 1.98, 12-21-2008
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * POWER-ON AF NOISE BURST:  This should now be eliminated.
\par 
\par * DIGIT 2 SWITCH TONE FEEDBACK RESTORED. The \lquote 2\rquote  key on the numeric
\par keypad now provides tone feedback when used for numeric entry or within
\par menu entries. There\rquote s no tone when it\rquote s used as \'d2REV\'d3 (temporary A/B VFO
\par reverse).
\par 
\par * SSB TX AFTER VFO A/B SWAP: Transmit filter settings are now correct
\par after any A/B swap, regardless of the modes of VFO A and B. This had been 
\par noted by some customers as a problem on power-up, but it could occur
\par anytime the VFOs were in different modes at the time of an A/B swap.
\par 
\par * INDEPENDENT PREAMP AND ATTN FOR SUB RECEIVER: The preamp 
\par and attenuator settings for the receiver are now independent of main. On each 
\par band, you can set up the sub\rquote s preamp/attenuator as desired using BSET. The 
\par sub\rquote s preamp/attenuator are separate even in diversity mode, where you\rquote ll 
\par often be using a lower-gain antenna for the sub receiver.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  A second tap
\par of A>B within the 2-second window still copies all main receiver settings to
\par the sub, including preamp and attenuator.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For software developers:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * \'d2FR0\'d3 COMMAND (SPLIT CANCEL): Now correctly restores the VFO A arrow icon.
\par 
\par * CONFIG:KPA3 MENU ENTRY: The parameter for this menu entry is now 
\par accessible via the \'d2MP\'d3 command.
\par   
\par * \'d2FA\'d3/\'d3FB\'d3 commands and loss of PLL lock: Large FA/FB frequency steps 
\par were, on rare occasion, causing loss of PLL lock. This has been corrected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * Added "PA$" (sub RX preamp) and "RA$" (sub RX attenuator) commands.
\par This is in conjunction with the sub preamp and attenuator settings now being
\par Independent of main (see above). During BSET, both return \'d2?;\'d3 at present.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.73 / DSP 1.98, 12-9-2008
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * RX EQ is now applied to both main and sub receivers.
\par 
\par * TUNE NO LONGER CANCELS AUTO-NOTCH.
\par 
\par * CONFIG:ADC REF MENU ENTRY:  This allows the operator to calibrate 
\par the voltage reference used by the K3 to measure and display certain values,
\par such as the rig\rquote s supply voltage. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 ADC REF calibration is optional but 
\par recommended}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 . First, disconnect anything attached to the ACC jack. Next,
\par locate the CONFIG:ADC REF menu entry. It will initially show }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 5.00}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  volts as
\par the reference voltage. Using a DMM set to DC volts, measure the actual
