\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf6\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\cf6\insrsid3036935  The following information is more accurate than the DVR instructions in the
\par K3 rev D owner\rquote s manual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * DVR ICON: The DVR icon (dual arrows--above the S-meter) turns on whenever 
\par the DVR is in use. The icon flashes slowly during all record operations, and quickly
\par during play.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs22\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * DVR TX MESSAGES: Message record, play and repeat are functional. (Message
\par chaining will be added in a subsequent release.) To start voice message record,
\par tap REC, then tap M1-M4. Record will start immediately. Tap M1-M4 again
\par to stop recording. To play a voice message, tap M1-M4. To repeat a voice message
\par (e.g., a CQ), *hold* M1-M4 rather than tap. Message play or repeat can be 
\par cancelled at any time by tapping REC.
\par 
\par * DVR RX {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}LOOP{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}:  Hold AF REC to start receive-audio recording. Hold AF REC
\par again to stop record. Up to 90 seconds of audio can be recorded; beyond this,
\par earlier audio will be overwritten. Hold AF PLAY to start playback; press any
\par switch to stop. VFO B will show the playback position in seconds, relative
\par to the most-recently recorded audio segment. During PLAY, you can move
\par forward/backward through RX audio loop buffer by rotating VFO B. An asterisk
\par (*) beside the seconds counter shows the extent  of the most recently recorded
\par segment. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  It is OK to record received audio continuously; this might be 
\par useful as a way of catching audio events that you wish to examine later.
\par Record will continue even if you transmit. However, at present, silence is recorded 
\par for the duration of any transmission.
\par 
\par * DVR RX {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}LOOP{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} PLAY IN TX MODE. First, enter voice transmit mode by holding
\par PTT or tapping XMIT. Then hold AF PLAY to start playback, and press any switch
\par to stop. CMP (speech compression) is automatically disabled. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  Playback 
\par volume of the RX loop buffer during TX mode is not yet adjustable. 
\par 
