\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * MAIN/SUB BALANCE CONTROL:  If CONFIG:SUB AF is set to BALANCE,
\par then the SUB AF GAIN control becomes a main/sub AF balance control when
\par the sub receiver is turned on (including diversity mode). In this case the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
\par AF GAIN controls the AF gain level for both receivers. When SUB AF is at
\par 12 o\rquote  clock, both receivers will be at full volume (main left, sub right). If SUB AF
\par is rotated fully counter-clockwise, you\rquote ll hear only the main receiver. If it\rquote s 
\par rotated fully clockwise, you\rquote ll hear only the sub receiver. At intermediate settings
\par you\rquote ll hear both. A BALANCE control is very useful for contesting and split 
\par operation. But it can also save a lot of AF gain control tweaking (i.e., matching 
\par main and sub), since MAIN AF controls both main and sub receiver audio.
\par 
\par * AGC-OFF AF LIMITER: An adjustable AF output limiter has been added
\par for operators who turn AGC off. This can protect your ears if a large signal 
\par appears. Signals or noise above the threshold will sound highly distorted
\par due to the limiting action, reminding you to back down the AF or RF gain.
\par The associated menu entry, CONFIG:AF LIM, defaults to NOR. Typical 
\par settings for those who often turn AGC off are 17 to 23, but some experimentation
\par will be required.
\par 
\par * DIGOUT0 SIGNAL (ACC connector): This now behaves as described in the 
\par owner's manual. When a transverter band is selected that is configured for
\par low-power operation (i.e., .01-1.50 mW, and using the KXV3\rquote s XVTR IN/OUT
\par jacks), DIGOUT0 provides a low-resistance path to ground that could be used to 
\par activate a small relay or other circuitry. At all other times the DIGOUT0 line 
\par will float (high-Z). If all transverter bands are configured for low power, then 
\par DIGOUT0 can be used as a \'d2transverter band selected\'d3 signal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * POWER LEVEL ON XVTR AND HF BANDS: Switching between HF and 
\par transverter bands no longer modifies the present HF band power setting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
