\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * FAST BAND SWITCHING USING KEYPAD:  We\rquote ve added a \'d2band select\'d3 
\par mode for memories 0-9. First, set CONFIG:MEM 0-9 to BAND SEL.
\par You can then use V>M to assign individual bands to keypad switches 0-9.
\par For example, use BAND UP/DN to get to 160 m, tap V>M, then tap #1.
\par From then on, tapping M>V, then #1, will take you to your last-used frequency
\par on 160 m, just as if you had used the BAND switches. Up to 10 of your favorite
\par bands can be assigned to keypad switches, including transverter bands. 
\par The behavior of memories 10-99 and the per-band quick memories (M1-M4)
\par will be unchanged.
\par 
\par * MAPPING OUT SELECTED BANDS:  You can now remove one or more bands
\par from the BAND UP/DN rotation using the CONFIG:BND MAP menu entry. Once
\par you\rquote ve located BND MAP, use BAND UP/DN to select bands, and set them to
\par IN or OUT using VFO A. (Works with transverter bands, too.) You can still 
\par get to mapped-out bands using memory recall, direct frequency entry, or 
\par computer-control commands (\'d2FA\'d3 and \'d2FB\'d3).
\par 
