\par * }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 A/B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 REV}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935  CAN NOW BE USED IN DIVERSITY MODE. In both cases, the
\par VFOs are swapped, allowing you to listen in diversity mode on VFO B\rquote s frequency.
\par 
\par * BSET IN DIVERSITY MODE: If you use BSET in diversity mode, you\rquote ll now
\par hear the main RX in the left ear and sub RX in the right. This is useful when using
\par SPLIT with diversity, as it allows you to override diversity mode temporarily and
\par listen to both your RX and TX frequencies.
\par 
\par * VFO B NOT LOCKED WHEN LINKED TO VFO A: This means the VFOs can
\par be linked but at different frequencies. A fixed offset can be established using
\par VFO B, and will be maintained as you tune VFO A.
\par 
\par * VFOs NOT LINKED IN DIVERSITY MODE: VFO A is used to update both
\par synthesizers (main and sub), but VFO B is now free to be used as a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}TX{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} 
\par frequency (see below). In DIVERSITY mode, the VFO A kHz decimal point slowly flashes, as before.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 Miscellaneous:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par * MESSAGE PLAY FIXES: There were a few issues with CW and DATA message
\par buffer playback, including occasional truncated characters when chaining in CW
\par mode, and inconsistent behavior when chaining.
\par 
\par * MORE ACCURATE AM-MODE POWER LEVEL. Also slightly higher modulation 
\par percentage.
\par 
\par * INTERNAL 2-TONE TEST GENERATOR now works with 2.7 as well as 2.8 
\par kHz crystal filters, and the tones are now correct when used with both LSB and USB. 
\par 
\par * KEY OUT disabled sooner on power-up: Previously, KEY OUT was active for 
\par about 3 to 4 seconds on power-up. This has been reduced to under one second.
\par In any case, no RF is present during this period.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 For Software Developers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 (see K3 Programmer\rquote s Reference, rev B14):
\par 
\par * \'d2DS\'d3 (VFO A DISPLAY READ): This command now correctly handles all of the
\par RX EQ / TX EQ \'d2mini-bar graph\'d3 levels as displayed in the main menu. The bar
\par graph level 1 character, if it appears in the \'d2DS\'d3 response string, is now converted
\par to an underscore rather than a semicolon. This preserves the semicolon as 
\par strictly a command terminator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * "DT" COMMAND ADDED (VFO A DATA sub-mode read/set). "MD" is 
\par still used to set norm/rev.
\par 
\par * "IF" COMMAND INCLUDES DATA SUB-MODE (K31 must be in effect).
\par 
\par * "IC" COMMAND ADDED (ICON and MISC STATUS): Provides state information on many functions, including BS
ET, TX TEST, VFO linking, diversity mode, sub RX antenna, full/semi QSK, dual-passband CW, dual-tone FSK filtering, ESSB, nose gate, FM PL tone on/off, etc. 
\par 
\par * \'d2LK$\'d3 COMMAND ADDED (VFO B LOCK).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\insrsid3036935 * \'d2TQ\'d3 (TRANSMIT STATUS QUERY) now returns 1 consistently when the K3 is in
\par transmit mode.
\par 
\par * MORE MENU ENTRIES ACCESSIBLE WITH \'d2MP\'d3 COMMAND: KAT3, VCO MD, and AGC THR are now available. See MN command table for details.
\par 
\par * KY (keying) remote control command now handles CR, LF, TAB and other
\par ASCII characters including:   [ \\ ] ^ _ `    All of these characters are useful in 
\par PSK D mode. They\rquote re ignored in other modes, except that  '_' becomes an
\par "AA" prosign in CW mode. 
\par 
\par * Prosign mapping (e.g., \'d2=\'d3 conversion to \'d2BT\'d3) is now disabled in PSK D 
\par and FSK D modes. This allows all ASCII characters to be transmitted normally.
\par (Prosigns can always be sent using the alphabetic characters themselves 
\par in these modes.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.46 / DSP 1.94, 10-3-2008
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * 40 METER PA CURRENT REDUCTION:  This revision corrects the low-pass 
\par filter configuration used on 40 m. The 10/12 LPF, not the 6 m LPF, is now used
\par in-line with the 40 m LPF. This optimizes return loss, keeping current at the
\par target level at 100 W (about 20 A).
\par 
\par * NOTE ON AM COMPRESSION: Starting with MCU 2.45/DSP 1.92, speech
\par compression has been disabled in AM mode. We hope to create a more effective
\par compressor for AM in a future revision; the original was adding distortion
\par without increasing \'d2punch\'d3. On the other hand, the available AM modulation level 
\par has been increased, and we\rquote re better utilizing the mic AGC system in this mode.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs22\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.45 / DSP 1.92, 9-29-2008
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * TRANSMIT NOISE GATE ADDED:  The TX noise gate can be used to suppress 
\par transmitted audio below a certain level, e.g. a noisy fan (not the one on the K3, of
\par course). To use the noise gate, locate CONFIG:TX GATE, tap \lquote 1\rquote  to turn it ON,
\par then use VFO A to set the desired threshold. Since there\rquote s no visual indication that 
\par transmit audio is below the threshold, you should adjust it using the transmit voice
\par monitor (MON), ideally using headphones. Set the threshold high enough to cut off 
\par transmit audio due to shack noise, but not so high that it causes your voice to drop
\par out too frequently. The TX GATE threshold can be adjusted in TX TEST mode.
\par 
\par * TRANSMIT INHIBIT (TX INH)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 FUNCTION IMPROVED: Activating the TX INH input 
\par on the ACC jack now asynchronously suspends RF output. It has no interaction
\par with transmit sequencing. When TX INH is active, the only indication is that the
\par \'d2TX\'d3 LCD icon flashes, as in TX TEST mode. This should closely match the transmit
\par inhibit logic of other transceivers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * COARSE TUNING CORRECTED: (1) Downward tuning with COARSE increments in 
\par effect occasionally resulted in the synthesizer unlocking, especially in AM mode with
\par 9-kHz European broadcast band increments. (2) Tuning down to the low end of
\par the K3\rquote s tuning range would cause quantization. For example, if you were at 505 kHz 
\par with 9 kHz steps selected and tuned downward one tic, the VFO would go to
\par 500 kHz, and the next upward tic would be 509 kHz. Both of these problems
\par have been corrected.
\par 
\par * \'d2VOX=OFF\'d3 REMINDER: Whenever you change the VOX setting from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 ON}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 OFF}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par in CW mode, then sometime later hit the key, you\rquote ll see a one-time \'d2VOX=OFF\'d3 
\par message. This is a subtle reminder that VOX must be turned on in CW mode to
\par enable hit-the-key operation. Otherwise you have to \'d2arm\'d3 the transmitter
\par by tapping XMIT or by using PTT. (This has always been the case for the K3, and 
\par most rigs behave in the same way.) We decided to add this reminder message because
\par operators not familiar with \'d2VOX for CW\'d3 have occasionally turned it off, only to wonder
\par later why the rig won\rquote t transmit in CW mode.
\par 
\par * TRANSMIT DISABLED DURING FIRMWARE LOADS:  You cannot key the 
\par transmitter during firmware loads, via KEY IN, PADDLE, PTT, XMIT, VOX, or 
\par computer commands. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 For Software Developers:
\par 
\par Note:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  Refer to the K3 Programmer\rquote s reference, rev. B10 or later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * "{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}OM{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}" COMMAND ADDED: Shows which K3 option modules are installed.
\par 
\par * "MP" COMMAND ADDED: Menu parameter direct read/set. Only applies to 
\par selected menu entries, as listed in the programmer\rquote s reference. 
\par 
\par * "MG" COMMAND ADDED: Mic gain read/set.
\par 
\par * "MD$" COMMAND ADDED: Sub RX/VFO B mode read/set.
\par 
\par * "IS;" COMMAND ADDED (I.F. shift). Note: In diversity mode, an IS or FW command
\par will be sent to both main and sub. In AI2 mode, moving the SHIFT or WIDTH controls 
\par will generate both IS and FW responses.
\par 
\par * \'d2FW0000x\'d3 form of the FW command can now handle x = 1 through 5 (requires
\par "K30" and "K22" be in effect; see programmer\rquote s reference.
\par 
\par * Added the following AI2 responses:  PC, AG, AG$, RG, RG$, NB, NORM (FW).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.38 / DSP 1.90, 9-7-2008
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * RIT CLEAR COMMAND: The \'d2RC\'d3 remote-control command now correctly
\par clears the RIT offset. It would sometimes do the equivalent of a \'d2long-hold\'d3 
\par of the CLR switch, copying the RIT offset to VFO A before clearing the offset.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.37 / DSP 1.90, 9-2-2008
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * FIRMWARE UPGRADE PROCESS IMPROVEMENT: When upgrading firmware, 
\par MCU and DSP code versions may temporarily become incompatible, resulting in
\par error messages during loads. These spurious errors are now suppressed, resulting
\par in a cleaner upgrade process, especially when upgrading from much older revisions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.36 / DSP 1.90, 9-1-2008
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * SUB/MAIN AF GAIN EQUALIZED. 
\par   
\par * VCO CAL improved to make synthesizer alignment easier.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.34, 8-29-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * CORRECTED SHIFT CONTROL DISPLAY. Center frequency was 
\par Incorrect in some cases.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.33, 8-28-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * DSP FILTER POSITION CORRECTED: At some bandwidth and SHIFT settings,
\par the DSP IF was shifted downward. Especially noticeable in CW mode.
\par 
\par * SHIFT CONTROL CW CENTER FREQ DISPLAY: If you\rquote re using a CW sidetone 
\par pitch that\rquote s not at a 50-Hz boundary, it will now be displayed accurately when the
\par SHIFT control is centered (i.e., when the asterisk appears).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.32, 8-28-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * CORRECTED ESSB/SSB PASSBAND ERROR (introduced in MCU rev. 2.31).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.31 / DSP 1.89, 8-28-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 New Features and Enhancements:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * CW SIDETONE INCREMENTS NOW 10 HZ (originally 50 Hz).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * RIT CLR switch now works during transmit in all modes and at any time.
\par 
\par * RIT CLR MENU ENTRY: You can use this menu entry to select \'d2UNDO ON\'d3 or
\par \'d2UNDO OFF\'d3. OFF is the default. When \'d2ON\'d3, tapping CLR will alternate between
\par 0.00 and the present RIT/XIT offset, if any.
\par 
\par * DIVERSITY RECEIVE MODE: If you have the sub receiver (KRX3 option) installed, 
\par you can take advantage of \'d2diversity receive\'d3 by using two separate receiving antennas.
\par This can improve signal copy during fading, and adds a spatial (L/R) effect to signals.
\par DIVERSITY MODE further enhances this capability by slaving the sub receiver\rquote s 
\par mode, filter settings, and VFO to the main receiver. To enter diversity mode, hold
\par SUB until you see \'d2DIVRSTY\'d3 on VFO B (about 2 seconds). The kHz decimal point
\par of the VFO A display will flash slowly as a reminder that diversity mode is in effect.
\par 
\par Notes on Diversity Mode:
\par 
\par 1. Entering diversity mode switches the sub receiver  to its AUX antenna
\par source. If you don\rquote t hear any right-channel audio, you probably don\rquote t have
\par an antenna connected to the sub\rquote s AUX input. Refer to the owner\rquote s manual
\par or KRX3 manual for information on sub receiver AUX antenna configuration.
\par 
\par 2. If your main and sub receiver have 5-pole crystal filters with differing frequency 
\par offsets, you may hear a slow phase modulation in the received audio at some
\par VFO frequencies. The only way to eliminate this effect is to use 5-pole filters with
\par matched offsets (available on request; contact Elecraft) or use 8-pole filters,
\par which have no offset.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 Miscellaneous changes:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * DUAL PB CW MIN CONTEXT BANDWIDTH NOW 400 Hz. In high-QRM situations,
\par a 400 Hz or 500 Hz crystal filter may be very useful as a limit to the context bandwidth.
\par Note that the \'d2pedestal\'d3 effect (-24 dB context filter) becomes more of a sloped 
\par response as the context bandwidth is reduced.
\par 
\par * DATA TX ALC IMPROVEMENTS. PWR control is now more responsive during
\par transmit in all DATA modes.
\par 
\par * FM SQUELCH THRESHOLD: Closely matched between main and sub receivers.
\par 
\par * NOISE BLANKER ON/OFF ON BAND CHANGE: The DSP noise blanker 
\par wasn\rquote t set up properly during band changes. It may have been left ON on the new
\par band in some cases.
\par 
\par * PA TEMP and FP TEMP are now "normal" VFO B alternate display modes, 
\par meaning that you don\rquote t have to set TECH MD to ON in the config menu.
\par 
\par * DDS frequency shifting during T/R changed to eliminate a variation in CW 
\par keying duty cycle that was occurring only over specific, narrow frequency ranges
\par on each band. This also eliminated a related CW keying artifact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 For software developers:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * RG$ command implemented (sub receiver RF gain). 
\par 
\par * "FA", "UP" ,"DN", \'d2RC\'d3, \'d2RU\'d3, and \'d2RD\'d3 COMMANDS UPDATE VFO B IF VFOS ARE LINKED (except in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}). These commands can also be used in transmit mode.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par MCU 2.23, 7-31-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par *LSB/USB TRANSMIT EQUALIZATION (experimental): Improved gain balance between LSB and USB. A 1 to 3 dB difference between the two had been reported with the 2.7 kHz (5-pole) filter. The passband should also be slightly flatter. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * ESSB (EXTENDED SINGLE SIDEBAND) ADDED:\~ Allows the K3 to transmit in SSB modes at a bandwidth o
f up to about 4 kHz. Requires a 6 kHz crystal filter on the RF board. Note: ESSB receive is obtained just by adjusting the WIDTH control. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 To enable ESSB transmit: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
(1) Make sure the 6 kHz filter is configured correctly for AM transmit; switch to AM mode, then specify this filter using CONFIG:FLTX AM. (A future firmware release should allow use of the FM filter for SSB as well, pending lab tests.) }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 (2) Locate CONFIG:TX ESSB. Select the desired extended bandwidth for SSB transmit (3.0 to 4.0 kHz) using VFO A. Then tap \lquote 1
\rquote  on the keypad to turn ESSB on/off. When on, the \'d2+\'d3 icon in the mode area will turn on. (If you turn ESSB on/off frequently, you might want to assign the TX ESSB menu entry to a programmable function switch.)    
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.22, 7-29-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * CHANNEL SCAN no longer locks out small encoders (during scan or after stopping it). 
\par 
\par * USER-DEFINED \'d2NORM\'d3 VALUES are now referred to as NORM1/2 rather than ALT1/2
\par   to avoid confusion with the \'d2ALT\'d3 switch, which is unrelated to NORM.
\par 
\par * FLASH MEMORY INITIALIZATION corrected to prevent spurious \'d2FPF LOAD 
\par   PENDING\'d3 message. If this message does appear unexpectedly, tap any switch
\par   to see the flash read exception code, e.g. \'d2FPF 1\'d3. Report this to customer support.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.20 / DSP1.88, 7-24-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * AGC: Slope is now approximately linear in dB.  Threshold 
\par   moved about 10 dB lower, closely matching earlier DSP revisions.
\par 
\par * NR: Gain levels re-balanced to account for changes to AGC.
\par 
\par * USER INTERFACE: Minor clean-up of menu entry text and parameters,
\par   help text, error messages, etc., to make operation more intuitive.
\par 
\par * SUB RX ON/OFF now has no effect on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}SPLIT{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, RIT, or XIT.
\par 
\par * SUB RX SYNTHESIZER is no longer updated when sub RX is turned off,
\par   even with VFOs linked. This prevents an audio artifact when tuning. Also
\par   eliminated interaction between main and sub synthesizers during T-R 
\par   switching that was causing keying artifacts at very specific frequencies 
\par   on some bands.
\par 
\par * IIR DSP FILTER ON/OFF SELECTION now applies to both main and sub
\par   receivers. (IIR filter on/off is selected by tapping the \lquote 7\rquote  switch while in the
\par   FLx BW menu entry. IIR filters apply only to 100 Hz and narrower DSP
\par   bandwidths. They have slightly more ringing than the default FIR filters.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.16, 7-9-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * SUB RCVR AUX ANT SELECTIONS: The ANT=ATU and ANT=BNC selections were
\par   reversed. You may need to set this up again (CONFIG:KXV3).
\par 
\par * SUB RCVR CONTROLS LINKED TO MAIN RCVR WHEN VFO {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}IND{\*\xmlclose}=NO: 
\par   BAND, PRE, ATTN, NB, NR, NOTCH. Attempting to change these (using BSET)
\par   results in "=MAIN" flashed on VFO B. Once we allow {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}VFO{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}IND{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}=YES, these
\par   controls will have individual settings in BSET mode. 
\par 
\par * SUB RCVR NB/NR/NOTCH WORKING: Setting up any of these functions for
\par   the main receiver sets them up for the sub receiver as well.
\par 
\par * RIT/XIT OFFSET NOT CLEARED WHEN SUB RCVR TURNED ON.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.15, 7-8-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * SYNTH TUNING CORRECTED ON 80 M: Downward tuning was sometimes 
\par   leading to loss of receive and/or transmit at certain frequencies.
\par 
\par * SYNC DATA: Selecting sync data or \'d2-S\'d3 (CONFIG:SYNC DT, used to minimize 
\par   the error rate of AMTOR, PACTOR, ARQ, and similar modes) now ensures that the 
\par   same crystal filter will be used for both RX and TX (either 2.7 or 2.8 kHz). While -S 
\par   is in effect, the receive crystal cannot be changed with XFIL, and SHIFT/LOCUT/HICUT
\par   are unavailable. WIDTH can still be changed, but it will affect only the DSP IF, not
\par   the crystal filter. The RX and TX 1st I.F.s will thus remain identical.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.14, 7-4-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * MEMORY RECALL ON 6 M (CW REV, etc.): Corrected problem with recall
\par   of CW normal/reverse and other parameters on 6 meters only.
\par 
\par * 50 AND 100 HZ bandwidths are now available in DATA A (for use 
\par   with PSK31 and other narrow modes).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.13 / DSP 1.83, 7-3-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par New Features:
\par 
\par * MEMORY ERASE: During memory recall or store, tapping CLR erases 
\par   the present numbered memory (00-99) and flashes "ERASED". You can 
\par   rotate VFO A to select and then erase any number of memories.
\par 
\par * POWER-UP KEY/PTT PROTECTION: If any external device attempts to key
\par   the transmitter within 2 seconds of power-up, "ERR KEY" or "ERR PTT" 
\par   will be shown on the VFO B display, and transmit will be inhibited. This applies
\par   to KEY IN, DOT, DASH, PTT, vox, or computer-initiated transmit (TX or KY
\par   commands). It should prevent accidental transmit during power-on when
\par   a computer, keyer, or other device is powered-up at the same time as the K3.
\par   Once all keying/PTT/vox activity has stopped, the message disappears,
\par   and normal transmit activity can be resumed.
\par 
\par Miscellaneous:
\par 
\par * RATE, FINE, and COARSE VFO tuning controls are all now saved
\par   per-mode rather than per-band/per-memory.
\par 
\par * ANTENNA CONTROLS are all now saved per-band, not per-memory. These include:
\par     - Main RX/TX antenna selection (1 or 2) 
\par     - Sub RX antenna selection ({\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose} or AUX)
\par     - RX ANT in/out selection
\par     - Preamp/attenuator settings for RX {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}ANT{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}ON{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and RX ANT OFF
\par     - DIGOUT1 menu parameter setting for ANT1 and ANT2
\par 
\par * PTT RLS MENU ENTRY (PTT release delay). This menu entry allows the
\par   the operator to specify a delay from release of PTT to exit from transmit 
\par   in voice and audio data modes. Not applicable to CW, FSK-D, or PSK-D.
\par   The default is 0. A higher value may be needed in ARQ and similar data modes,
\par   where the transmit DSP \'d2pipeline\'d3 must be fully processed before the 
\par   carrier is dropped.
\par  
\par * NARROW CW/DATA FILTERS (100/50 Hz): Corrected distortion and loss issues.
\par 
\par * SYNTHESIZER: {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}VCO{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}CAL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} improvements related to \'d2ERR VCO\'d3 and \'d2ERR PL1\'d3 
\par   error messages.
\par 
\par For software developers:
\par 
\par * '$' character in CAT commands targets the sub receiver. At present only the
\par   AG$ command is implemented (sub AF gain, e.g. AG$;  AG$050;).
\par 
\par * "}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af38\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f38\fs20\insrsid3036935 FI}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 " command provides last four digits of the K3\rquote s exact I.F. center frequency, in Hz.
\par   For example, if the selected filter has an offset of 0.00 and is not shifted, the I.F.
\par   is exactly 8215000, and \'d2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af38\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f38\fs20\insrsid3036935 FI}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 ;\'d3 will return \'d2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af38\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f38\fs20\insrsid3036935 FI5000;}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 \'d3.
\par 
\par * "MD" COMMAND DURING \'d2TUNE\'d3: For the duration of TUNE, the MD command 
\par   will return the operating mode that was in effect at the time TUNE was activated,
\par   not CW mode. This should fix a problem with third-party panadapters
\par   that may have seen TUNE as a mode change to CW.
\par 
\par Sub receiver:
\par 
\par * KRX3 MENU ENTRY: Settings now include NOT INST, ANT=BNC, ANT=ATU. When
\par   the sub receiver is installed, the operator must select one of the two \'d2ANT\'d3 settings based
\par   on what is connected to the KRX3\rquote s \'d2AUX RF\'d3 input: the KAT3\rquote s non-transmit antenna
\par   (ANT=ATU) or the rear-panel AUX RF BNC jack (ANT=BNC).
\par 
\par * BSET-MODE ANT1/2 ICONS:  When the sub receiver turned on, you can use BSET mode
\par   to view or change the sub\rquote s antenna assignment: {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}MAIN{\*\xmlclose} (sharing the main receiver\rquote s 
\par   antenna) or AUX (using the sub\rquote s AUX RF input). When AUX is selected, the ANT1/2 icons
\par   will either turn off (if ANT=BNC was specified for in the KRX3 menu entry) or one of
\par   them will be on (if ANT=ATU was specified). 
\par 
\par * SUB RX FILTER SETUP: In menus, toggling between RF and SUB and switching 
\par    filters or modes now properly sets up sub if applicable. This allows the operator to hear
\par    the effect of any changes on the sub receiver\rquote s own filters (if SUB AF GAIN is set
\par    so it can be heard). NOTE: You must turn the sub receiver ON before entering the
\par    menu if you want to listen to the sub during filter changes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.10 / DSP 1.81, 6-22-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * SYNTHESIZER OCCASIONAL RX/TX DROP-OUTS FIXED.
\par 
\par * SYNTHESIZER BANDSWITCHING DELAY increased to allow VCO more time to lock.
\par 
\par * TX/RX switching time improvement in DATA-S mode.
\par 
\par * NARROW FIR FILTERS: Gain balanced (CW and data modes).
\par 
\par * NOISE BLANKER can now be used with AGC turned off in all modes. 
\par 
\par * DENOISER: Gain balance improved in SSB/AM modes. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.03 / DSP 1.78, 6-9-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 Misc:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * EXT ALC voltages adjusted to match resistors called out in EXT ALC mod document.
\par   
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 PC Control Command Changes (for application software developers):
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * "PC" (PWR READ) IN K22 MODE now supplies correct value for QRO (KPA3) on/off.
\par 
\par * \'d2FA/FB\'d3 BAND CHANGE now saves mode for old band before switching to new band. 
\par    This prevents problems with per-mode bandwidth, etc., following band changes.
\par 
\par * \'d2MD\'d3 COMMAND FIXED:  On 6 m, CW norm/reverse were being reported backwards. 
\par   On all bands, DATA A and PSK-D were reversed for both get and set (AFSK A and 
\par   FSK-D were correct). }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 NOTES:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  When an \'d2MD\'d3 command is used to switch between 
\par   data normal and reverse, it applies to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 both}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  DATA A and PSK-D (if either of these was
\par   in effect), or AFSK A and FSK-D (if either of these was in effect). To get/set data
\par   modes, use \'d2SWH43;\'d3 to emulate pressing the DATA MD switch, then \'d2DB\'d3 to retrieve
\par   the data mode text string from VFO B, and \'d2UPB;\'d3 / \'d2DNB;\'d3 to change the mode. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.02, 6-7-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * VOX SWITCH NOW FUNCTIONS CORRECTLY IN CW MODE. When VOX is OFF in
\par   CW mode, transmit must be enabled via XMIT or PTT rather than just hitting the key.
\par 
\par * MEMORY-BASED CHANNEL HOPPING (for 60 m in particular):  This now works
\par   as described in the K3 Owner\rquote s Manual (rev C., page 37). You can manually \lquote hop\rquote  
\par   with VFO A, or scan channels. First, store the desired channels in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 adjacent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  memories. 
\par   For example, you might set up 60-m channels in memories 61-65 (5330.5 kHz, etc.).
\par   Next, change the first label character in each of these memories to an asterisk (*) as 
\par   described in the manual. (The first memory }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 above}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
below}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  your channel-hop group
\par   must either have no asterisk in their first label position, or be on different bands.) 
\par   Finally, tap M->V and select any one of these memories. Manual rotation of VFO A 
\par   and scanning will then use only the memories in the group. To return to normal operation, 
\par   use any of the VFO rate switches, or change bands. NOTE: A future revision will allow 
\par   FM channel hopping based on squelch activity.
\par 
\par   SCANNING TIP: On a noisy band, scanning may pause too often. Try using a narrower 
\par   filter, turning the preamp off, or backing down RF GAIN until the scan starts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 2.00 / DSP 1.77, 6-6-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * BAND DATA FOR TRANSVERTERS: The BAND0-3 outputs on the 15-pin ACC jack
\par   can now be used to control transverters as described in the Owner\rquote s Manual (revision
\par   C, page 18-19). To enable this feature, set }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:KIO3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  to HF-TRN (which outputs
\par   band decode data for both HF and transverter bands) or TRN (transverter band
\par   data only). The default is NOR (HF band decodes only).
\par 
\par * CW MODE SPEAKER ARTIFACT ELIMINATED: Some operators reported
\par   a periodic burst of noise coming from the speaker when headphones were
\par   used in CW mode. This has been corrected.
\par 
\par * MIC BUTTON FUNCTIONS DEFAULT TO OFF:  There\rquote s now a menu entry for
\par   turning the mic up/down buttons on or off (}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:MIC BTN}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 ). The default is OFF, 
\par   which makes these buttons inactive. You should turn it ON only if you have a
\par   mic whose up/down buttons provide contact closures to ground, with no resistors
\par   in series or in parallel (such as a Kenwood MC-43). Some mics have internal 
\par   resistors and are not compatible with the K3\rquote s up/down feature. If you try to
\par   use such a mic (by setting CONFIG:MIC BTN to ON), VFO A may scan continuously.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.99 / DSP 1.76, 6-4-08   
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par New Features & Misc. Changes:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * POWER LOSS DURING TRANSMIT ON 6 M CORRECTED.
\par 
\par * RIT APPLIES TO BOTH VFOs WHEN LINKED. With the sub receiver installed,
\par    this allows diversity receive tuning via RIT while preserving a fixed transmit frequency.
\par 
\par * ANTIVOX GAIN increased. (Some antivox users may need to use a lower setting.)
\par 
\par * MIC UP/DOWN buttons, if provided on your mic, will move VFO A up or down one
\par   unit at the present tuning rate. Holding the UP or DOWN buttons for about 1 second
\par   will auto-repeat the VFO movement, allowing manual scanning of the current band.
\par 
\par * PER-BAND POWER CONTROL:  This feature is very useful with external amplifiers
\par   as well as transverters. To use it, change }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:PWR SET}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  to PER-BAND.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * RECEIVE RFI DETECTION: If the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:RFI DET}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
 menu entry is set to
\par   NOR (normal), the K3 will detect the presence of very large signals (about 2 watts or 
\par   higher) that appear at the ANT1/2 jacks }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 in receive mode}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 . \'d2HI RFI\'d3 will be displayed 
\par   on VFO B. Try separating antennas, using single-band filters, or reducing power. 
\par   To disable RFI detection, set }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:RFI DET}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  to OFF (not recommended).
\par 
\par * EXTERNAL ALC:  We strongly recommend that external ALC only be used to protect 
\par   your amplifier during operation into a failed load or other serious condition. In fact, most 
\par   amplifiers have such protection built in, and do not need or specify the use of ALC. 
\par   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 ALC should not be used as a way to clip or compress fast voice peaks.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  The K3\rquote s
\par   ALC uses a moderate attack time specifically to prevent signal distortion due to ALC
\par   action, so it is the responsibility of the operator to keep drive below this level.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\ul\insrsid3036935 DO NOT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  SET THE K3\rquote 
s POWER LEVEL TO MAX AND ADJUST AMP OUTPUT USING
\par   THE AMP\rquote s ALC CONTROL. THIS WILL RESULT IN SPLATTER AND KEY CLICKS. 
\par   INSTEAD, ADJUST THE DRIVE ON EACH BAND SO IT\rquote S JUST BELOW THE LEVEL 
\par   WHERE ALC STARTS TO ACTIVATE. (See Per-Band Power Control, above.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 NOTE: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
You may need to make some simple modifications to the transceiver to use 
\par   external ALC. This information will be added to our K3 mods page. Information for 
\par   specific amplifiers will be made available when possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935   Once the mods have been made, set }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:EXT ALC}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
 to ON by tapping \lquote 1\rquote . (6 m can be 
\par   turned on/off separately from HF.) The default external ALC threshold of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 -4.0}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 V will work 
\par   in most cases, but can be changed if required.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 If your amplifier\rquote s gain varies from band 
\par   to band, you may want to set }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:PWR SET}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  to PER-BAND. You can then adjust
\par   the drive ideally on each band to prevent external ALC activation during normal operation.
\par   If you select CMP/ALC metering, external ALC activity is indicated by 8 or more bars. 
\par   If you select SWR/RF metering, the CMP/ALC meter icons will flash during external ALC 
\par   activity to make you aware of the condition. Reduce the drive power if this occurs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 PC Control Command Changes (for application software developers):
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par * BAND CHANGES RESULTING FROM FA/FB commands now run to completion before 
\par   any additional commands are processed (such as MD or FW). This should prevent 
\par   errors in mode or filter settings which sometimes occurred with older K3 firmware.
\par   Band changes take approximately 0.5 seconds to complete.
\par 
\par * FA/FB COMMANDS TARGETING 6 METERS will select a 6 m transverter if available. 
\par   If not, these commands will select the K3\rquote s internal 6 m band.
\par 
\par * FW (filter bandwidth) command fully implemented. If K3 extended command mode is
\par   in effect (\'d2K31;\'d3), FW sets or reads bandwidth in 10-Hz increments. 
\par 
\par * DS (VFO A/icon read) now reports a number of K3-specific icon states, including 
\par   RX ANT, SUB, etc. See K3 Programmer\rquote s Reference, revision B2 or later.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.96, 5-14-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * NEW VFO COARSE TUNING RATES: FM, 10 kHz; CW, 0.1 kHz; SSB, 0.1 kHz.
\par 
\par   * SQUELCH ASSIGNED TO SUB RF/SQL now persists across a power cycle.
\par      (This is done using CONFIG:SQ MAIN; set it to \'d2=SUB POT\'d3.)
\par 
\par   * XVn ON menu entry, when assigned to a programmable function switch, will
\par     will now alternate between YES and NO. This now applies to all 2-valued menu entries.
\par 
\par   * Flash and EEPROM memory read/write are now verified to improve reliability
\par     of parameter storage. This includes PLL data tables, frequency memories, etc.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.94 / DSP 1.73, 5-12-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * VOX: Increased sensitivity. Typical VOX GN settings now ~30-50.
\par 
\par   * VOICE MONITOR: Eliminated \'d2scratchy\'d3 artifacts with compression set to high levels.
\par 
\par   * FM DEVIATION ADJUSTABLE:  Use }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 CONFIG:FM DEV}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  menu entry (default: 5.0 kHz).
\par 
