\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935   * SSB RECEIVE PASSBAND EXTENDED AT LOW END (now 100 Hz; was 200 Hz).
\par 
\par   * AM RECEIVE WIDTH RANGE INCREASED:  The WIDTH control in AM mode now has
\par     a range of 2.8 to 10.0 kHz. Wider settings provide outstanding fidelity for hi-fi speech 
\par     and other wide-band signals. This is the *IF* filter bandwidth -- the traditional way to show 
\par     bandwidth for AM, because the required IF bandwidth is twice the modulation bandwidth.
\par     NORM selects an IF bandwidth of 6.0 kHz in this mode. WIDTH settings above 6.0 kHz
\par     will not be useful unless you have an FM-bandwidth crystal filter installed (at FL1).
\par 
\par   * IF A 2.8 KHZ FILTER IS INSTALLED, SSB "NORM" BW is 2.8 kHz (was fixed at 2.7 kHz).
\par 
\par   * AUTO-SPOT (SPOT with CWT ON) now works with both very weak and very strong signals.
\par 
\par   * PSK AUTOTUNE ACCURACY improved. You may still need to use RIT (FINE steps) to 
\par     tune in signals for best built-in text decode. (Also see CW-to-DATA in the Owner\rquote s Manual.)
\par 
