\par 
\par   * POWER ROLLBACK BASED ON REFLECTED POWER:  Power rollback begins at about 
\par     2.5:1 at 100 W (and of course much higher SWRs are tolerated at lower power settings).
\par     Recovers to original target power level after mismatch is corrected.
\par 
\par   * CW QSK further refined, with smoother mute/unmute in the presence of QRN and QRM.
\par 
\par   * SSB TRANSMIT BANDPASS EXTENDED AT LOW END. Improvement is about 2 dB 
\par     at 300 Hz, 3 dB at 200 Hz, and 6 dB at 100 Hz. Additional improvement possible via TX EQ.
\par 
\par   * SSB TX POWER CONTROL improved. Set ALC for about 5 bars (rarely 6+) using MIC gain
\par     control, then set CMP and POWER as desired. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 The RF power bargraph shows approx.
