\par   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * SSB TRANSMIT Improvements: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par 
\par     This is the first phase of our effort to make SSB transmit setup and use more consistent
\par     with operator expectaions. Changes so far include:
\par 
\par         - Higher signal-to-noise radio at both mic jacks, as well as LINE IN
\par         - Livelier and easier to use transmit-mode metering (CMP, ALC, SWR, POWER)
\par         - Better optimized TX EQ menu function
\par         - More effective compression (CMP)
\par         - Greatly reduced distortion with CMP set to 0 (for audio data modes, high-fidelity
\par           speech, and two-tone testing with an external audio generator)
\par 
\par     (Planned for next release:  Improved low-frequency response and adjustable TX passband.)
\par     
\par     }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 Note on MIC gain setup:  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 To properly adjust MIC gain, first set CMP to 0, then adjust
\par     MIC gain for about 5 bars on the ALC meter (it should not hit 6 bars during normal speech).
\par     Then set CMP for the desired compression amount.
\par 
\par  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935  * 2 USER-DEFINED "NORM" filter setups for each mode: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par     Now, in addition to the K3's "NORM" values, you can save two of your own often-used filter
\par     setups in each mode, and recall them using the NORM function. The new NORM values
\par     are named ALT1 and ALT2. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 To save a filter setup}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 , hold NORM until you see "<- SAV ->"
\par     (3 seconds), then rotate the knob left or right to save it as ALT1 or ALT2. (The arrows to the
\par     left and right of "SAV" are a reminder that you can rotate the knob left or right go get to the
\par     "ALTernate" filter memories.) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 To recall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 , hold NORM until you see "<- NOR ->" (about 
\par     1/2 second), then rotate the knob left or right to recall ALT1 or ALT2. Note: Whenever
\par     you normalize the filter passband via NORM, ALT1, or ALT2, two "wings" appear on the 
\par     DSP filter passband graphic. Moving any DSP control makes the wings disappear, as a 
\par     reminder that the passband is no longer normlized.
\par 
\par   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 * DUAL PASSBAND Bandwidth Restore: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 On exit from DUAL PB, the previous CW bandwidth 
\par     is restored.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.73 / DSP 1.56, 3-1-08}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * BETTER MIC JACK S/N RATIO:  This is the first of several changes intended to
\par     improve voice transmit performance. (Other changes are still in the works.) This change
\par     increases the gain ahead of the transmit A/D converter, which should result in lower 
\par     quantization noise, especially with mics that have low output. Still experimental.
\par                               
\par   * SPEAKER "popping" eliminated when using headphones and certain combinations of
\par     features (such as NR).  
\par  
\par   * VFO LINKING: Holding the "SUB" switch links/unlinks the two VFOs. When linked,
\par     VFO A is the master; turning it moves both VFOs the same amount. VFO B can be 
\par     set to the same frequency by tapping A>B, or it can be offset a fixed amount from VFO A.
\par     Setting them to the same frequency will permit diversity receive with the subreceiver.
\par 
\par   * LOCUT/HICUT CONTROL RANGE: DSP controls are better behaved, preventing 
\par     "wrap-around" and other reported anomalies.
\par 
\par   * Tapping A>B in SPLIT mode now updates the filter settings correctly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.70, 2-20-08}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * [#94] ATU MATCHING IMPROVED: If operator taps ATU TUNE a second time on the same 
\par     band/antenna within 5 seconds, a more extensive search is used. Dramatically improved 
\par     performance in tests with some high-Q (narrow-band) loads. Original (fast) algorithm 
\par     is unchanged. 
\par 
\par   * [#243] RIT/XIT OFFSET DISPLAY MODE ADDED (right after date, before voltage). This is 
\par     especially useful with CW-to-PSK31, where the operator may be quite conscious of the 
\par     required RIT offset, or for those using RIT during contesting.
\par 
\par   * [#322] RTTY CWT INDICATOR UNSTUCK (was getting stuck when PITCH was accessed).
\par 
\par   * [#275] Tapping XMIT during CW message playback both stops the message *and* exits 
\par     transmit mode.
\par 
\par   * [#199] SSB filter BW steps now 100 Hz up to 3 kHz, then 200 Hz.
\par 
\par   * [#292] NON-VOX CW no longer has any delay after transmit termination (i.e., release of 
\par     PTT or exit from XMIT).
\par 
\par   * [#236] Switching of antennas during tune is not allowed (this was fixed some time ago).
\par 
\par   * [#285] Tapping transmit-related multifunction encoders briefly displays the present parameter 
\par     value (SPEED/MIC/CMP/PWR). Double-tap to display the existing parameter (since this
\par     switches first to the alternate, then back).
\par 
\par   * [#305] Tapping filter-related multifunction function encoders briefly displays the present
\par     parameter value (SHIFT/LOCUT/HICUT/WIDTH). Double-tap to display the existing parameter.
\par 
\par   * TRANSMIT BLOCKED from 7.500 to 8.999 MHz (to prevent possible damage to the 
\par     KAT3/KANT3 traps). This range is blocked even if the customer has unblocked transmit using
\par     our software "MARS enable" utility. It is only usable in milliwatt-power mode (KXV3).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.69, 2-18-08}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * Fixed problem with CW transmit via the KEY jack, where short-duration noise pulses
\par     or very fast CW could result an incorrect synthesizer frequency on return to receive.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.68/DSP 1.53/DTBL0008, 1-30-08}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * CW-to-PSK transmit added. It works, but now that QSOs are possible in this mode, 
\par     we need to look into the +10 to +16 Hz receive offset reported by users.  
\par   * "UP" and "DN" remote control commands now work for parameter setup, such as NB, 
\par     TEXT DEC, DATA MD, NR ADJ, etc. Adding 'B' (e.g., "UPB;", "DNB;") controls the 
\par     VFO B parameter; otherwise, the VFO A parameter is controlled. 
\par   * DATA MODE selection is now stored per-band, per-memory.
\par   * MIC Source is now independent for voice/data modes. See micCtrlVoice, micCtrlData.
\par   * Milliwatt power display now correctly shows "-9.0" dB between -8 and -10.
\par   * Synthesizer control improvements (eliminated some ERR VCO cases during VCO CAL,
\par     as well as 30-m transmit problems).
\par             
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.66, 1-29-08}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * CORRECTED ATU TUNE PROBLEM: In version 1.65, tapping ATU TUN would use the value
\par     set in the new TUN PWR menu entry, and afterward set the power knob to the TUN PWR value.
\par     The ATU TUNE power level is supposed to be fixed (5W and 10W, automatically controlled).
\par     It should not be affected by either the TUN PWR menu entry or the power knob.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid3036935 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f37\fs20\cf2\insrsid3036935 MCU 1.65 and DSP 1.52, 1-28-08
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid3036935 
\par   * TUNE POWER level menu entry (TUN PWR). This determines the power level used 
\par     when the TUNE switch is pressed. The default, "NOR", uses the power knob setting.
\par     Alternatively, the value can be set to any power level from 0.1-120 W.
\par 
\par   * REAL-TIME-CLOCK display now keeps accurate time. The RTC IC itself was running
\par     accurately, but the VFO B time display was running about 9% slow.
\par 
\par   * MODE SWITCH now only cycles thorugh one sideband (LSB or USB) on each band -- 
\par     not both. Saves time when switching modes, especially useful in contest situations.
\par     Use the ALT switch (hold the left end of MODE) to switch between LSB and USB (per-band).
\par     NOTE: As a result of this change, you may need to re-select the desired sideband on 
\par     some bands. You'll only have to do this once.
\par 
\par   * S-METER ACCURACY Improved. Suggest using SMTR SC=14 and SMTR OF=24 
\par     (these are the normal defaults).
\par 
\par   * EXTERNAL CW TIMING IMPROVED: Corrected rise/fall time assymmetry. Internal
\par     and external keyers should now be closely matched in weighting.
\par     NOTE: You may need to reduce the weight of external keying, if you had increased
\par     it to compensate.
\par 
\par   * AMTOR RX/TX turnaround times improved. To do this, we've created a variation of
\par     SSB and DATA modes called SYNC DATA. It should only be used with modes like
\par     AMTOR that require the fastest possible turnaround time. To turn on SYNC DATA, first
\par     locate the SYNC DT menu entry (SYNC DATA), and assign it to any programmable
\par     function switch (PF1, PF2, M1 tap or hold, M2 tap or hold, etc.). Then use this 
\par     programmable switch to enable SYNC DATA. The -S mode icon appears. This setup
\par     can be enabled separately for SSB or DATA modes. (The actual turnaround times will
\par     vary with crystal filter selection. Further improvements may be possible and are being
\par     explored.)
\par                     
